---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Hi, I'm Sunil Mayya 👋</h1>
			<p>
				I'm a software engineer at Mozilla working on Firefox — primarily the
				web platform and networking. Day to day that means implementing
				web-platform features in Gecko and taking part in the standards
				conversations (WICG, IETF, W3C) that shape them.
			</p>
			<p>
				A lot of my recent work sits at the boundary between the browser and the
				network:
				<a href="https://wicg.github.io/local-network-access/">Local Network Access</a>,
				<a href="https://wicg.github.io/nav-speculation/speculation-rules.html">Speculation Rules</a>,
				HTTP <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Reference/Headers/No-Vary-Search">No-Vary-Search</a>,
				the <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API">Fetch API</a>
				(including <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/RequestInit#keepalive">keepalive</a>),
				and <a href="https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/WebTransport">WebTransport</a>.
				I enjoy the parts of the job that don't make it into the release notes —
				the design tradeoffs, the cross-vendor disagreements, and the
				implementation details you only discover once you try to ship the thing.
			</p>
			<p>
				I write here about that work — browser internals and web standards
				explained from the inside. Away from the editor I spend a fair bit of
				time in the kitchen, so you'll also find cooking recipes here, alongside
				the occasional post about life in general.
			</p>
			<p>
				Have a look at the <a href="/blog/">blog</a>, read a bit more
				<a href="/about/">about me</a>, or say hello at
				<a href="mailto:smayya@mozilla.com">smayya@mozilla.com</a>.
			</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
